Pemex May End Repsol Pact If Sacyr Sells Shares, Economista Says

-- B y   B e n   S i l l s
-- 
2011-10-13T06:10:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/pemex-may-end-repsol-pact-if-sacyr-sells-shares-economista-says.html
Petroleos Mexicanos  may end its pact
with  Sacyr Vallehermoso SA (SYV)  to vote together on the board of
 Repsol YPF SA (REP)  should the construction firm reduce its stake in
Repsol, El Economista reported.  Sacyr’s lenders, who are mulling whether to refinance a 4.9
billion-euro ($6.8 billion) credit line that comes due in
December, and some of its board members are pressing Chairman
Luis Del Rivero to sell Repsol shares to reduce the company’s
borrowing needs, the newspaper said.  “If Sacyr doesn’t manage to refinance its debt the
agreement disappears,” El Economista cited Pemex director Juan
Jose Suarez Coppel as saying.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Sills at 
 bsills@bloomberg.net  